Package orientationStructures

Class DirectedToNNDigraph

java.lang.Object
orientationStructures.SparseGraphDataPreparer
orientationStructures.DirectedToNNDigraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
NearestNeighborsDigraphSupplier
public class DirectedToNNDigraph extends SparseGraphDataPreparer implements NearestNeighborsDigraphSupplier
Takes a List of StringPairWithWeight records, indexes the source and target objects by integers 0 to n − 1, and builds a SparseIntDirectedWeightedGraph object. After extracting the two core, build K-NN digraph.
Author:
R. W. R. Darling

    • kNearNbrOfVertex

      public Stream<org.jgrapht.alg.util.Triple<Integer,Integer,Double>> kNearNbrOfVertex(int v, int k)
      Method to return source, target, weight triples for the k outgoing edges from source v with largest weight. If v has out-degree less than k, all out edges are returned. These streams are flattened, over all source vertices in the two core, in the buildKNearNbrDigraph(int) method.

      Excludes non-two core edges.

      Parameters:
      v - source vertex
      k - number to be returned
      Returns:
      k outgoing two core edges from source v with largest weight., or empty stream if v is not in the two core.

    • buildKNearNbrDigraph

      public void buildKNearNbrDigraph(int k)
      For every vertex in the two core, the k OUTGOING two core edges of highest weight will be placed in a list, from which a new sparse directed linkageGraph, this.knnDigraph, is built. We cannot delete some edges from this.digraph, which is immutable.
      Specified by:
      buildKNearNbrDigraph in interface NearestNeighborsDigraphSupplier
      Parameters:
      k - number of neighbors
